HEADWORD: Perilla
<hw>Pe*ril"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of labiate herbs, of
which one species (<spn>Perilla ocimoides</spn>, or <spn>Perilla
Nankinensis</spn>) is often cultivated for its purple or variegated
foliage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

